$ Excel: Page Layout -> Themes

Select the preferred visual theme or schemes.

These themes and schemes are stored in the following locations:
table { lll
   ☰ ~Path~ ☰ → development/filename-extensions[File extension]
   Theme ☰ → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-Office/root/Document-Themes-vv[`C:\Program Files\Microsoft Office\root\Document Themes vv`] ☰ `.thmx`
   Colors scheme ☰ → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-Office/root/Document-Themes-vv/Theme-Colors[`C:\Program Files\Microsoft Office\root\Document Themes vv\Theme Colors`] ☰ `.xml`
   Fonts scheme ☰ → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-Office/root/Document-Themes-vv/Theme-Fonts[`C:\Program Files\Microsoft Office\root\Document Themes vv\Theme Fonts`] ☰ `.xml`
   Effect scheme ☰ → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-Office/root/Document-Themes-vv/Theme-Effects[`C:\Program Files\Microsoft Office\root\Document Themes vv\Theme Effects`] ☰ `eftx`
table }

With → development/languages/VBA, these themes and schemes can be set with
code {
ActiveWorkbook.ApplyTheme("C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Office\root\Document Themes 16\Ion Boardroom.thmx")
ActiveWorkbook.Theme.ThemeColorScheme.Load("C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Office\root\Document Themes 16\Theme Colors\Blue.xml")
ActiveWorkbook.Theme.ThemeFontScheme.Load("C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Office\root\Document Themes 16\Theme Fonts\Arial.xml")
ActiveWorkbook.Theme.ThemeEffectScheme.Load("C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Office\root\Document Themes 16\Theme Effects\Reflection.eftx")
code }
